# Backend (Cloudflare Pages Functions) — LOCAL values for `npm run dev:full`.
# Copy to `.dev.vars` (git-ignored) and fill in. wrangler loads these as
# bindings on c.env. In production set the same names as Pages env vars
# (RESEND_API_KEY as a *secret*; the *_CLIENT_IDS are public and may be plain vars).
# See docs/AUTH_SETUP.md.

# --- Resend (the only real secret) ---
# Without RESEND_API_KEY the backend logs the OTP and returns it as `devCode`
# instead of sending an email.
RESEND_API_KEY=
# Verified sender. Resend's shared onboarding@resend.dev only delivers to the
# Resend account owner's address; use a verified domain for real users.
RESEND_FROM=Ping-Pong Club <onboarding@resend.dev>

# --- OAuth accepted audiences (comma-separated, PUBLIC) ---
# The backend verifies each OIDC id_token's `aud` against these lists.
# Google: include every client id that can issue a token — web + iOS + Android.
GOOGLE_CLIENT_IDS=
# Apple: include the web Service ID *and* the native app bundle id
# (com.ppclub.app), since their id_tokens carry different `aud` values.
APPLE_CLIENT_IDS=
